# /usr/culture/arts_and_media/
# Humanity's attempt to process its own existence.
# Art is not a luxury — it is the error log of consciousness.
#
# Cave paintings at Lascaux: 17,000 years old.
# Before writing, before agriculture, before cities:
# humans painted animals on walls by firelight.
# The drive to represent is older than civilization.
#
# Functions of art:
#   - Mirror: reflect reality back to the viewer
#   - Window: show realities the viewer hasn't experienced
#   - Hammer: shape reality by changing how people think
#   - Playground: explore possibility without consequence
#   - Prayer: reach toward something beyond comprehension
#
# "All art is quite useless." — Oscar Wilde
# He meant this as the highest compliment.
# Art exists for itself. That is its radical proposition.
# In a world where everything must justify its existence
# through utility, art says: I am sufficient.
#
# Mediums evolve:
#   Oral tradition → Writing → Printing → Photography →
#   Film → Radio → Television → Internet → VR → AI-generated
#
# Each new medium was denounced by the previous one.
# Socrates warned that writing would destroy memory.
# He was right. And it was worth it.
#
# The medium IS the message (McLuhan, 1964).
# Instagram didn't just distribute photos — it changed
# what people photograph, how they see, what they value.
# The tool reshapes the hand that holds it.
